tags.description: On December 12, 1887, the land which is now labeled Crocus Park was designated as public land in the Riverside Addition plat. The park is used as a passive recreational area.
tags.name: Crocus Park

tags.description: On December 12, 1887 the land which is now identified as Willow Park was so designated as public land in the Riverside Addition plat. The .36 acre plat has a small open space area and limited play apparatus.
tags.name: Willow Park

tags.inscription: In all, 198 State School children have been laid to rest in the State School Cemetery. The Cemetery is open for public viewing, weather permitting. It has been restored by the Orphanage Museum and local friends.
tags.name: Children's Monument
